<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     07-19 0086</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0088</SECOND>
<HEAD>Correspondent Appointed in El Paso</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EL PASO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Suzanne Gamboa, a newswoman in the Dallas
bureau of The Associated Press, has been appointed AP correspondent
in El Paso.
   The appointment was announced Tuesday by Dallas Chief of Bureau
John Lumpkin.
   Ms. Gamboa, 25, joined the AP as a summer intern in Dallas in
1985. She is a native of Goldsboro, N.C., and a graduate of the
University of Texas.
   She succeeds Holden Lewis, who recently was appointed
correspondent in Lubbock.
</TEXT>
