<SECOND>PM-Thailand-Explosion,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bomb Blast Kills 11 in Thailand</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded in front of a courthouse
in a northeastern city today, killing 11 people and injuring eight,
police said.
   The bomb, placed in the basket of a parked bicycle, exploded at
11:40 a.m. as the victims were descending the stairs of the
courthouse in Nakhorn Ratchasima, a police officer said.
   ``It's probably a homemade bomb with remote control,'' said the
officer, who demanded anonymity.
   He said the attack was probably related to a business dispute.
One of the businessmen involved and several of his bodyguards were
among those killed by the bomb, the police officer said.
   Three people were seriously injured, and five others suffered
less serious wounds, the officer reported.
   He said no arrests were made.
   Nakhorn Ratchasima, capital of the province of the same name, is
130 miles northeast of Bangkok.
