<SECOND>PM-BRF--United Accident,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>DC-10 Slides off Runway; No Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A United Airlines DC-10 with 249 people aboard
slid 300 yards off a runway after landing at rain-soaked O'Hare
International Airport, but there were no injuries, authorities said.
   After touching down Tuesday night, the pilot could not brake the
jet in time to avoid running off the runway into a grassy, muddy
area, said Lisa Howard, a spokeswoman for the Chicago Department of
Aviation.
   Flight 247, bound from Cleveland to Denver, landed in Chicago
with a crew of 10 and 239 passengers, said United spokesman Joe
Hopkins.
   Airport workers used portable staircases to evacuate the
passengers within 15 minutes, Ms. Howard said.
   O'Hare had been experiencing delays most of the afternoon due to
severe thunderstorms in the area, and the accident caused flights to
be delayed on all major carriers for up to 1{ hours, Ms. Howard said.
