<HEAD>Smuggler Who Swallowed Heroin in Bag Dies of Overdose</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMMAN, Jordan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Egyptian trying to smuggle heroin through
Jordan died after he swallowed a plastic bag of the drug and it
leaked inside his body, the kingdom's anti-narcotics chief said
Wednesday.
   The 25-year-old man, who was not identified, was in a coma for
five days before he died Saturday at Amman's Bashir Hospital, said
Col. Ghaleb Zoubi.
   Blood tests conducted while the man was in the coma ``proved that
the victim's body absorbed large quantities of a drug,'' he said.
   During an autopsy, police found heroin wrapped in four small
plastic bags.
   An investigation showed the drug was being smuggled to Egypt via
Jordan, Zoubi said.
   Authorities say Jordan does not have a drug problem and that 90
percent of drug trafficking cases involve Jordan as a transit point
for narcotics smuggled from Turkey and Lebanon to ``Arab markets.''
