<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--LaScala     07-19 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--La Scala,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>La Scala Chooses Verdi for Opening Night</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Verdi's ``Sicilian Vespers'' will inaugurate
the opera season at La Scala on Dec. 7, the theater announced
Wednesday.
   The theater said Riccardo Muti will direct an international cast
at the opening performance that will include Chris Merritt and
Cheryl Studer of the United States, Paata Burchuladze of the Soviet
Union and Giorgio Zancanaro of Italy.
   ``Sicilian Vespers'' will be the first of two Verdi works the
Scala intends to offer during the season. In April, Muti and film
director Liliana Cavani will defy tradition and present their
version of ``La Traviata.''
   ``We want to destroy the taboo according to which certain works
cannot be presented again at the Scala after memorable versions like
the one with (Maria) Callas,'' said artistic director Cesare
Mazzonis.
   Moscow's Bolshoi Theater will offer the Milan audience four
Russian works. In June, Seiji Ozawa will close the season with
Tchaikovsky's ``Queen of Spades.''
</TEXT>
