<FIRST>u a BC-WorstUSCrashes     07-19 0206</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Worst US Crashes,0215</SECOND>
<HEAD>List of Ten Worst U.S. Plane Crashes</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of the worst plane crashes in the U.S. history:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   May 25, 1979 _ American Airlines DC-10 crashed after takeoff at
O'Hare International Airport in Chicago; 273 killed.
   Aug. 16, 1987 _ Northwest Airlines MD-80, crashed on takeoff at
Detroit Metropolitan Airport; 156 killed.
   July 9, 1982 _ Pan AM Boeing 727 crashed after takeoff in Kenner,
La.; 153 killed.
   Sept. 25, 1978 _ Pacific Southwest Airlines Boeing 727 and
private Cessna 172 collided over San Diego; 144 killed.
   Aug. 2, 1985 _ Delta Air Lines Lockheed L-1011 crashed at
Dallas-Fort Worth International Airport; 137 killed.
   Dec. 16, 1960 _ United DC-8 and TWA Super-Constellation collided
over New York City; 134 killed.
   June 30, 1956 _ TWA Super-Constellation and a United DC-7
collided over the Grand Canyon in Arizona; 128 killed.
   June 24, 1975 _ Eastern Airlines Boeing 727 crashed in a storm at
Kennedy Airport in New York City; 113 killed.
   Sept. 4, 1971 _ Alaska Airlines Boeing 727 crashed into a
mountain near Juneau, Alaska; 111 killed.
   Dec. 29, 1972 _ Eastern Airlines Lockheed Tristar crashed on
approach to Miami International Airport; 101 killed.
</TEXT>
