a broad coalition of U.S. churches to fight drugs, homelessness and
AIDS.
   He told the denomination's biennial meeting that acting together,
Christians ``can make a difference.'' He urged them to ``stop
arguing over the nature of the Bible and begin to hear it and obey
it.''
