certain kinds of desktop personal computers to non-communist
countries, and will propose eliminating similar restrictions on
exports to East Bloc nations.
   Commerce Secretary Robert Mosbacher disclosed the plans Tuesday,
calling them the partial result of President Bush's trip to Europe
earlier this month, which included stops in Poland and Hungary.
