<FIRST>r f PM-DuPont-Fuji     07-19 0288</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-DuPont-Fuji,0300</SECOND>
<HEAD>DuPont, Fuji Acquire Pre-Press Printing Business</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Crosfield is cq.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   DuPont Co. and Fuji Photo Film Co. Ltd.
announced they have acquired the pre-press printing business of
Crosfield Electronics Ltd. from De La Rue Co. PLC for $370 million.
   The deal, disclosed Tuesday, is subject to approval by De La Rue
shareholders and government agencies. The agreement was signed in
London.
   De La Rue will retain the Crosfield press controls business.
   ``Crosfield pioneered the electronic pre-press industry and both
DuPont and Fuji are very enthusiastic about joining this proud
tradition of innovation,'' said Clifford H. Schwieter, business
director of DuPont's electronic imaging systems.
   ``We believe that the combination of our worldwide resources in
electronic color pre-press will significantly enhance Crosfield's
ability to deliver the highest value systems and services available
in the market.''
   Mike Ricciuto, DuPont spokesman, said the DuPont and the
Tokyo-based Fuji have not determined what share of Crosfield each
will have.
   ``We haven't really settled on the structure. We will be putting
together the way it will be operated. This is an evolution of our
relationship established last year,'' Ricciuto said.
   Crosfield Electronics was founded in 1947 and acquired by De La
Rue in 1974. It has 3,200 employees and its 1988 revenues were
nearly $400 million. Its principal manufacturing plants are in
Manchester, N.H., Minneapolis, and Boston, and Peterborough, Hemel
Hampstead and Milton Keynes, England.
   Crosfield is a world-wide market leader in high-resolution
electronic color systems for the pre-press market. It has an
extensive integrated digital color equipment line.
   DuPont and Fuji are leading suppliers to the graphic arts
industry. In May 1988, DuPont and Fuji formed a joint development
agreement to produce medium-resolution color electronic equipment.
</TEXT>
