   The consensus estimate on Wall Street had called for a 0.3
percent June increase.
   Though the latest figure came as no dramatic surprise, analysts
said, it bolstered hopes that the Federal Reserve might soon relax
its credit policy further.
   The news helped push interest rates lower in the government
securities market today.
   Gainers among the blue chips included General Electric, up } at
55; American Telephone &amp; Telegraph, up \ at 36}; McDonald's, up \ at
30], and International Business Machines, up ] at 115[.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
.81 to 185.72. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up .79 at 370.96.
   On Tuesday the Dow Jones industrial average fell 8.73 points to
2,544.76.
   Declining issues outnumbered advances by about 7 to 5 on the
NYSE, with 618 up, 865 down and 519 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 152.35 million shares, against 131.96
million in the previous session.
