<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-UnitedTechnologies     07-19 0213</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-United Technologies,0224</SECOND>
<HEAD>UTC Earnings Slightly Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   United Technologies Corp. said Wednesday
its second-quarter earnings were nearly flat compared with last
year's.
   United Technologies reported its second-quarter income edged up
0.5 percent to $197.3 million from $196.2 million in the
corresponding 1988 quarter. Earnings per share held steady at $1.50.
   Revenue grew 17.8 percent to $5.3 billion from $4.5 billion in
the second quarter of 1988.
   Last year's second quarter results included a one-time pretax
gain of $41.4 million, representing United Technologies' share in
the sale of Telefunken Electronic GmbH, a semiconductor joint
venture.
   ``Our second-quarter financial performance reflects better
year-to-year operating results and improved earnings quality,'' said
Robert F. Daniell, United Technologies chairman and chief executive
officer.
   After-tax income for the first six months of 1989 totaled $321
million, or $2.45 a share, up 0.9 percent from $318 million, or
$2.44 a share, in the first half of 1988.
   Revenue in the first half amounted to $9.7 billion, up 10.2
percent from $8.8 billion in the same period last year.
   United Technologies said it had a business backlog on June 30
valued at $17.5 billion.
   United Technologies, based in Hartford, is the parent company of
Pratt &amp; Whitney aircraft, Sikorsky helicopter, Carrier air
conditioners and Hamilton Standard.
</TEXT>
