<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-AMR     07-19 0210</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-AMR,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>AMR's Quarterly Earnings Set Fourth Consecutive Record</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Record traffic on American Airlines in
June pushed parent AMR Corp.'s quarterly profit to $177.9 million, a
25.8 percent increase over last year's second quarter, the company
said Wednesday.
   The Fort Worth-based company said earnings were $2.83 per share,
on total operating revenue of $2.72 billion. In the quarter ended
June 30 of last year, AMR earned $141.4 million, or $2.36 per share,
on revenue of $2.16 billion.
   ``This represents our fourth consecutive quarter of record
earnings,'' Chairman Robert L. Crandall said.
   Crandall said June was the best traffic month in the company's
history, with June 30 its busiest day ever.
   American had 21.8 percent share of the domestic market during the
quarter, continuing its recent claim to the nation's largest
carrier, Crandall said.
   Revenue yield per passenger mile, a key industry gauge, improved
in the quarter from 11.84 cents to 12.17 cents. The company's
passenger load factor also increased from 64.6 percent to 65.3
percent.
   For the first half of the year, AMR has earned $278.9 million, or
$4.43 per share, on revenue of $5.17 billion, compared to $209.8
million, or $3.49, on revenue of $4.13 billion in the first half of
last year.
</TEXT>
