<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-ChampionInternational     07-19 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Champion International,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>Earnings Up 1.7 Percent In 2nd Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Champion International Corp. said
Wednesday its second-quarter earnings eged up 1.7 percent despite
operating problems at several of its pulp and paper mills.
   The wood products company posted second-quarter earnings of $114
million, or $1.16 per share, compared with $112 million, or $1.15 a
share, a year earlier.
   Second-quarter revenue rose 1.6 percent to $1.28 billion compared
to $1.26 billion last year.
   For the first six months, Champion earned $227 million, or $2.32
a share, on sales totalling $2.6 billion. In the first six months of
1988, the company earned $214 million, or $2.19 a share, on revenues
of $2.5 billion.
   ``Difficulties in bringing rebuilds back on line and other
operating problems marred what would otherwise have been a better
second quarter and first half,'' said Andrew C. Sigler, chairman and
chief executive officer.
</TEXT>
