<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Polaroid     07-19 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Polaroid,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Polaroid Earnings Rise Nearly $18 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Polaroid Corp. reported Wednesday that
earnings rose nearly $18 million in the second quarter, despite
costs associated with fighting off hostile suitor Shamrock Holdings.
   The Cambridge-based film and camera manufacturer said it spent $2
million in battling Shamrock during the quarter.
   For the quarter, earnings totaled $42.7 million, or 62 cents a
share, on revenue of $91.9 million, compared with earnings of $24.8
million, or 40 cents a share, on revenue of $45.7 million a year
earlier.
   Earlier this year, Polaroid successfully fought off a $3.1
billion takeover bid by investor Roy E. Disney's Shamrock Holdings.
   Polaroid also reported that revenues from instant film and
videotape sales increased during the quarter, and it expanded the
distribution of the company's conventional film line, Polaroid
OneFilm, which was introduced in April.
</TEXT>
