<FILEID>AP-NR-07-19-89 2318EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-GTE     07-19 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-GTE,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>GTE Second Quarter Earnings Up 10 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GTE Corp., citing increased growth of its
telephone business, Wednesday reported second-quarter earnings of
$329 million, up 10 percent over the $299 million earned in the same
period last year.
   Earnings per share in the quarter were 98 cents compared with 87
cents a share in the 1988 quarter, while revenue rose 3 percent to
$4.3 billion, up from $4.2 billion for the same period a year ago.
   For the first half of the year, net income increased 12 percent
to $658 million, or $1.96 a share, up from $586 million, or $1.71 a
share, in the first six months of last year.
   Revenue increased 4 percent in the first half compared to the
same period last year, from $8.2 billion to $8.4 billion.
   Revenue from telephone operations increased 6 percent in the
second quarter to $3.1 billion.
   ``This strong second-quarter performance is particularly
gratifying in light of the continuing competitive and regulatory
pressures faced by our major businesses,'' said James L. Johnson,
chairman and chief executive officer.
</TEXT>
